  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the onion into chunks and the peppers into strips. Add a splash of olive oil to a large saucepan set over a medium heat (or a wok with a lid), then add the onion and peppers and cook until softened."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Crush the garlic, finely chop half of the chilli (or more/less, depending on how spicy you want it!), leaving the other half for topping later, and add to the pan. Dice up the chicken into bite-sized chunks, increase the heat and and stir the chicken through the saucepan. Cook for around 5 mins until slightly browned. Meanwhile, rinse the uncooked rice."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the curry powder, peanut butter, honey, soy sauce, lime juice, stock and rice. Stir and bring to the boil. Cover and reduce the heat to low, leave to cook for 10 mins. After 10 mins pour in the coconut milk, re-cover and cook for a further 10 mins. Remove from the heat and leave covered for 5 mins to steam."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While it’s cooking, crush up the nuts, slice the chilli and spring onion. To serve, divide the rice between bowls and top with the nuts, chillies and spring onion."
    }
  ],
